comments: Firstly, everything happened quickly! I the quickness and the subtle changes in letters and colours (ie. theree quickly changeable variables made it challenging to keep up. It was challenging to 'tune' into the language as such, and this mirrors learning a new language for the first time- you can listen and watch intently, but can miss a lot simply because you can't tune in. Memory alone isn't a strategy, and so I was picking a few that I could 'bank' and definitely remember and then hoping that my conscious and subconscious would be able to pick up some other patterns. In the long run, the only way to learn this is with repeated practise to allow that 'magic click' to happen where everything just suddenly fits in; like a language.
